1 Sec. 19. The legislative body of the designated unit shall file a
2 certified copy of the plan with each of the following at the same
3 time certifications are made under section 18 of this chapter:
4 (1) The county recorder of each county in which a
5 reorganizing political subdivision is located.
6 (2) The department of local government finance.
7 (3) The clerk of the circuit court.
8 Sec. 20. Each county recorder receiving a certification under
9 sections 18 and 19 of this chapter shall record the certification and
10 the plan of reorganization in the records of the county recorder
11 without charge. The county recorder shall notify the county
12 election board of each county in which the township is located.
13 Sec. 21. (a) The township is reorganized under the conditions set
14 forth in the plan of reorganization filed with the county recorder
15 under this chapter.
16 (b) This subsection applies if the designated unit is a
17 municipality. If the municipal legislative body fails to adopt a
18 reorganization plan not later than December 31, 2026, the
19 township shall reorganize with the county in which the township is
20 primarily located. The county fiscal body shall:
21 (1) prepare a reorganization plan for adoption by the county
22 fiscal body that takes effect January 1, 2028; and
23 (2) take all other steps necessary under this article.
24 The county fiscal body has all of the powers and authority under
25 this chapter to prepare and implement a township reorganization
26 plan without the approval of the township.
27 Sec. 22. The department of local government finance is
28 expressly directed to complete the duties assigned to it under
29 IC 6-1.1-17-16 with respect to the submitted property tax levies,
30 property tax rates, and budget as follows:
31 (1) For each budget year, not later than December 31 of the
32 year preceding that budget year, unless a taxing unit in a
33 county is issuing debt after December 1 in the year preceding
34 the budget year or intends to file a shortfall appeal under
35 IC 6-1.1-18.5-16.
36 (2) For each budget year, not later than January 15 of the
37 budget year if a taxing unit in a county is issuing debt after
38 December 1 in the year preceding the budget year or intends
39 to file a shortfall appeal under IC 6-1.1-18.5-16.
40 Sec. 23. (a) This section applies to a reorganization under this
41 chapter that involves:
42 (1) a municipality as the designated unit; and
