21 Sec. 24. (a) A designated unit has the powers granted by statute
22 to a township, including a power described in subsection (b).
23 (b) Except as provided in the plan of reorganization, a
24 designated unit may do any of the following:
25 (1) Establish any fund that the township (either acting on its
26 own or jointly with another political subdivision) was
27 authorized to establish before January 1, 2028.
28 (2) Impose any tax levy or adopt any tax that the township
29 was authorized to impose or adopt before January 1, 2028.
30 Sec. 25. A plan of reorganization may establish within the
31 township, territories, or districts:
32 (1) in which specified services provided by the designated unit
33 will be provided at different levels, quantities, or amounts;
34 and
35 (2) in which the fees, charges, or taxes imposed by the
36 designated unit will vary depending on the level, quantity, or
37 amount of the services provided.
38 Sec. 26. The following apply:
39 (1) Indebtedness that was incurred by the designated unit or
40 township before January 1, 2028:
41 (A) may not be imposed on taxpayers that were not
42 responsible for payment of the indebtedness before
