1 (ii) the maximum levy growth quotient applicable for
2 property taxes first due and payable in 2028; plus
3 (B) any amounts borrowed by the township under
4 IC 36-6-6-14(b) or IC 36-6-6-14(c) in 2027.
5 Sec. 28. (a) Except as provided in subsections (c) through (d), a
6 political subdivision may not take an action described in subsection
7 (b) within a township after December 31, 2026.
8 (b) A political subdivision may not take any of the following
9 actions partially or wholly within a township after December 31,
10 2026, unless the designated unit agrees by adopting a resolution:
11 (1) Initiate an annexation of territory.
12 (2) Establish a fire protection territory or fire protection
13 district.
14 (3) Extend water, sewer, or any other infrastructure to the
15 political subdivision.
16 (4) Expand zoning jurisdiction under IC 36-7-4-205.
17 (c) This chapter does not prohibit a designated unit from taking
18 an action under subsection (b) for the purpose of implementing the
19 plan of reorganization.
20 (d) A political subdivision may take an action described in
21 subsection (b) after December 31, 2027.
22 Sec. 29. (a) Except as otherwise provided in this section, until
23 the final plan of reorganization is approved by the legislative body
24 of the designated unit, the designated unit or township may not
25 promote a position on the reorganization by doing any of the
26 following:
27 (1) Using facilities or equipment, including mail and
28 messaging systems, owned by the designated unit or township
29 to promote a position on the reorganization, unless equal
30 access to the facilities or equipment is given to persons with a
31 position opposite to that of the designated unit or township.
32 (2) Making an expenditure of money from a fund controlled
33 by the designated unit or township to promote a position on
34 the reorganization.
35 (3) Using an employee to promote a position on the
36 reorganization during the employee's normal working hours
37 or paid overtime, or otherwise compelling an employee to
38 promote a position on the public question at any time.
39 However, if a person described in subsection (c) is advocating
40 for or against a position on the reorganization or discussing
41 the reorganization as authorized under subsection (c), an
42 employee of the designated unit or township may assist the
2026 IN 1315—LS 6995/DI 87

11
1 person in presenting information on the reorganization if
2 requested to do so by the person described in subsection (c).
3 However, this section does not prohibit an official or employee of
4 the designated unit or township from carrying out duties with
5 respect to a reorganization that are part of the normal and regular
6 conduct of the official's or employee's office or agency, including
7 the furnishing of factual information regarding the reorganization
8 in response to inquiries from any person.
9 (b) This subsection does not apply to:
10 (1) a personal expenditure to promote a position on a
11 reorganization by an employee of the designated unit or
12 township whose employment is governed by a collective
13 bargaining contract or an employment contract; or
14 (2) an expenditure to promote a position on a reorganization
15 by a person or an organization that has a contract or an
16 arrangement (whether formal or informal) with the
17 designated unit or township solely for the use of the political
18 subdivision's facilities.
19 A person or an organization that has a contract or arrangement
20 (whether formal or informal) with the designated unit or township
21 to provide goods or services to the designated unit or township may
22 not spend any money to promote a position on the reorganization.
23 A person or an organization that violates this subsection commits
24 a Class A infraction.
25 (c) Notwithstanding any other law, an elected or appointed
26 official of a designated unit or township may:
27 (1) personally advocate for or against a position on a
28 reorganization; or
29 (2) discuss the reorganization with any individual, group, or
30 organization or personally advocate for or against a position
31 on a reorganization before any individual, group, or
32 organization;
33 so long as it is not done by using public funds. Advocacy or
34 discussion allowed under this subsection is not considered a use of
35 public funds.
36 SECTION 3. An emergency is declared for this act.
